==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incurvate
<hw>In*cur"vate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incurvatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>incurvare</ets> to crook; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>curvus</ets> bent. See <er>Curve</er>, and cf.
<er>Incurve</er>.]</ety> <def>Curved; bent; crooked.</def>
<rj><au>Derham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incurvate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Incurvate
<hw>In*cur"vate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Incurvated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Incurvating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To turn from a
straight line or course; to bend; to crook.</def>
<rj><au>Cheyne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

